<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-20-0057 </DOCNO><TEXT>Environmental law is discussed from its instrumental and other aspects.Two main categories of problem are pointed out. One comprises problemsof a general nature, e.g. legal rights to be observed in all fields ofenvironmental law. The other comprises a variety of individual problemsin the field of environmental protection law. The author presents a comparativeinvestigation aiming at a systematisation, harmonisation and furtherimprovement of environmental law. (HSCH).</TEXT></DOC>